.TH TLDR "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tldr \- Bash client for tldr pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tldr
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tldr
is a bash client for tldr-pages, providing simplified and community-driven man pages. It shows practical examples of how to use common command-line tools.
.PP
The script fetches concise help pages that focus on practical examples rather than comprehensive documentation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tldr tar
Show tldr page for tar
.TP
.B tldr git
Show tldr page for git
.TP
.B tldr --update
Update tldr cache
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/tldr/settings.conf
User configuration file for tldr preferences
.TP
.B ~/.cache/tldr/
Cache directory for tldr pages
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error or page not found
.TP
.B 4
Network connection failed
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Simplified command documentation
.IP \(bu 2
Focus on practical examples
.IP \(bu 2
Community-maintained pages
